# Testing Standards

## Test Pyramid

```
E2E (Playwright)        → critical user journeys only
Integration tests       → API routes with real DB (test DB)
Unit tests (Vitest)     → services, utilities, transformations
```

## Unit & Integration Tests (Vitest)

### File Locations

```
apps/api/tests/         → Vitest specs (*.test.ts)
apps/api/test/unit/     → Unit specs
apps/api/test/integration/ → Integration specs (node --test)
apps/api/test/security/ → Security specs (node --test)
sercop-unified/frontend/src/**/*.test.tsx  → Component/service tests
```

### Vitest Patterns

```typescript
import { describe, it, expect, beforeEach, vi } from 'vitest';

describe('TenderService', () => {
  beforeEach(() => {
    vi.clearAllMocks();
  });

  it('returns paginated list with correct total', async () => {
    const mockDb = { tender: { findMany: vi.fn().mockResolvedValue([...]) } };
    const service = new TenderService(mockDb as any);
    const result = await service.list({ page: 1, pageSize: 10 });
    expect(result.total).toBe(42);
    expect(result.data).toHaveLength(10);
  });
});
```

### Coverage Targets

| Layer | Minimum |
|-------|---------|
| Service/utility functions | 80% |
| Route handlers | 70% |
| React components | 60% |

Run coverage: `npm run test:coverage` in each package.

## E2E Tests (Playwright)

### Config Files

| Config | Scope |
|--------|-------|
| `playwright.config.ts` | Default full suite |
| `playwright.admin.config.ts` | Admin flows (runs in CI) |
| `playwright.battery.config.ts` | Battery/regression suite |
| `playwright.evidence.config.ts` | Evidence capture runs |

### Spec Pattern

```typescript
import { test, expect } from '@playwright/test';

test.describe('Tender search', () => {
  test.beforeEach(async ({ page }) => {
    await page.goto('/');
  });

  test('supplier can search and view tender detail', async ({ page }) => {
    await page.getByRole('searchbox').fill('construcción');
    await page.getByRole('button', { name: 'Buscar' }).click();
    await expect(page.getByTestId('tender-list')).toBeVisible();
  });
});
```

### Accessibility in E2E

```typescript
import AxeBuilder from '@axe-core/playwright';

test('main page has no critical a11y violations', async ({ page }) => {
  await page.goto('/');
  const results = await new AxeBuilder({ page }).analyze();
  expect(results.violations.filter(v => v.impact === 'critical')).toHaveLength(0);
});
```

## Smoke Tests

```bash
npm run smoke   # scripts/smoke.js — quick health check against running stack
```

Run after every deployment as a post-deploy gate.

## Do / Don't

- ✅ Mock external HTTP calls in unit/integration tests (use `vi.mock` or MSW)
- ✅ Use a **separate test database** — never run integration tests against dev/prod DB
- ✅ Test error paths, not just happy paths
- ✅ Use `getByRole` / `getByTestId` in Playwright (not CSS selectors)
- ❌ Never `console.log` in tests — use `expect` assertions
- ❌ Never hardcode test data IDs — use fixtures or factories
- ❌ Never skip flaky tests with `test.skip` — fix or remove them
